---

## If the Expected Result Is Wrong

The expected result breaks when a required document gains or loses a section. This is intentional — a changed document should break the check until nhash is updated.

When verification fails, the reconciliation process is:

1. Recount sections in every required document carefully. A section is any `## Section N —` heading.
2. Report your counts to the user: "AGENTS.md: [n] sections, BUGS.md: [n] sections, NEXT_SESSION.md: [n] sections."
3. Recalculate: X (total sections) × Y (documents) × 5.
4. Report the new result to the user and ask: "Should I update nhash to [new result]?"
5. Do not update nhash yourself. Wait for explicit human approval.
6. After approval, update nhash expected result and report: "nhash updated. Verification system is current."

The human decides whether the section change was intentional. An agent never silently reconciles a hash mismatch.

